Why 4-stars when there are so many mediocre reviews? We went there for lunch today with friends (Saturday). I think they open at 11 or 11:30 and we left a little before 2:00. We were the only ones there??? The service was excellent (the upside of being the only customers). We had the chicken pot pies and the chicken and dumplings. Both were terrific. The wines were great and reasonable. Frankly, I think this place would do better in a different location than a strip mall (parking isn't great) and they changed the name. I told the waiter I was giving them 5-stars but they were out of some of the menu items our friends wanted so I am backing down to 4. You can't sell it if you don't have it. Seems I learned that in business school or somewhere.

